["189579"]={["Title"]="", 
    ["1"]="Though access to the Sepulcher continued to elude me, I learned much by observing the automa.\\r$B\\r$BAdmittedly, I underestimated them at first. They seemed mere servitors, less capable of independent thought than even the muddle-minded attendants in Oribos!\\r$B\\r$BBut like everything else in Zereth Mortis, they were part of a pattern. A geometry that shifted, expanding and contracting as demanded by the duty put before them.",
    ["2"]="\"After all, this land is no museum",
    ["3"]="Do you see? Do you understand as I do?\\r$B\\r$BEverything about the Shadowlands--everything!--is part of the pattern. A closed system in which nothing is lost. Even that which is seemingly destroyed is merely being reshaped for a new purpose.\\r$B\\r$BPurpose. Hmm. Myopic though they are, perhaps the attendants understand some small measure of this mystery.",
